verse.lines:
{lang-eng}I am Thine, O Lord, I have heard Thy voice,
And it told Thy love to me;
But I long to rise in the arms of faith
And be closer drawn to Thee.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}To the cross where Thou hast died.
Lord,
To Thy precious, bleeding side.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Consecrate me now to Thy service, Lord,
By the power of grace divine;
Let my soul look up with a steadfast hope,
And my will be lost in Thine.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}There are depths of love that I cannot know
Till I cross the narrow sea;
There are heights of joy that I may not reach
Till I rest in peace with Thee.{/lang-eng}
